[320.534378, "i", "perl -0777 -pi -e 's/allMoves := append\\(append\\(\\[]MoveRow\\{\\}, freshMoves\\.\\.\\.\\), resumeMoves\\.\\.\\.\\)/\\/\\/ The audit compares fresh vs resume internally, but the case output (and\\n\\/\\/ the records\\/log sidecars) must reflect a single resolved move stream in\\n\\/\\/ order, not a concatenation of both paths.\\n\\/\\/\\n\\/\\/ Using a single canonical stream also avoids spurious duplicates when the\\n\\/\\/ fresh and resumed runs agree (the expected clean state).\\nallMoves := append(\\[]MoveRow\\{}, freshMoves\\.\\.\\.)/s' /app/internal/exec/run.go\n"]
[320.536836, "o", "perl -0777 -pi -e 's/allMoves := append\\(append\\(\\[]MoveRow\\{\\}, freshMoves\\.\\.\\.\\), resumeMoves\\.\\.\\.\\)/\\/\\/ The audit compares fresh vs resume internally, but the case output (and\\n\\/\\/ the records\\/log sidecars) must reflect a single resolved move stream in\\n\\/\\/ order, not a concatenation of both paths.\\n\\/\\/\\n\\/\\/ Using a single canonical stream also avoids spurious duplicates when the\\n\\/\\/ fresh and resumed runs agree (the expected clean state).\\nallMoves := append(\\[]MoveRow\\{}, freshMoves\\.\\.\\.)/s' /app/internal/exec/run.go\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
